7 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Qualifications for appointed commissioners -- definitions. (1)
8 Appointed commissioners are meant to be industry experts.
9 (2) An appointed commissioner must have a minimum of 2 years separation from any professional
10 affiliation with an entity or affiliated company of an entity that is subject to regulation by the commission.
11 (3) An appointed commissioner, spouse, or minor children may not have financial interests in any
12 entity or affiliated company of an entity that is subject to regulation by the commission.
13 (4) An appointed commissioner must be a citizen of the United States and must have resided in
14 the state of Montana for a minimum of 2 years immediately prior to appointment.
15 (5) An appointed commissioner must have professional experience in an industry and no two
16 commissioners may claim experience from the same industry. During the confirmation hearing, the senate must
17 confirm that an appointee meets the experience requirement. Determinations on experience are at the sole
18 discretion of the senate.
19 (6) An appointed commissioner may not serve on a political party committee, have held or run for
20 elected office with any political party in the previous 2 years, or have been employed by a political party,
21 political committee, or political party committee in the previous 2 years.
22 (7) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
23 (a) "Experience" means employment, a board position, or a related activity within an industry.
24 (b) "Industry" means science, technology, engineering, or math fields, and public accounting or
25 property and utility valuation and finance professions.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Process for appointing commissioners. (1) As provided in 69-1-103,
28 commissioners are to be appointed by the governor and confirmed by the senate.
