1 (2) (a) An entity that is subject to regulation by the commission may put forward candidate
2 suggestions to the governor for consideration. The governor is not obligated to choose a candidate
3 recommended by a regulated entity.
4 (b) Political parties, political committees, and political party committees may not put forward
5 candidate suggestions to the governor for consideration.
6 (3) The governor shall ensure that candidates meet the requirements provided in [section 5] before
7 announcing their nomination.
8 (4) (a) During the confirmation process, the senate shall confirm that the governor's assessment of
9 the candidates' qualifications is accurate. The senate may also explore the ethics and fitness for office of the
10 candidates.
11 (b) The senate may not refuse an appointment based on criteria not listed here or in [section 5].
12 The senate may not refuse an appointment because an industry, as defined in [section 5], is not represented,
13 so long as no industry is represented by two or more appointees.
