15 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Transition. (1) The commissioners in office on the effective date of [this
16 act] shall serve out the remainder of their respective terms.
17 (2) (a) On the effective date of [this act], the commissioner for the second district becomes the
18 commissioner for the eastern congressional district and the commissioner for the third district becomes the
19 commissioner for the western congressional district. These commission seats will remain election positions
20 pursuant to 69-1-103.
21 (b) A commissioner elected at the general election in 2028 and in subsequent elections serves a
22 2-year term as provided in 69-1-105.
23 (3) No later than January 1, 2027, the governor shall appoint commissioners to fill the seats for the
24 current first and fifth districts when the current commissioners' terms end.
25 (4) No later than January 1, 2029, the governor shall appoint a commissioner to fill the seat for the
26 current fourth district when the current commissioner's term ends.
